mappings.name: Get list of products for a query

products.description: With this beautiful design piece you will never miss an appointment anymore. Yay.

correction.description: Object with information of misspelled terms.

misspelled.description: Whether the term is misspelled (`true`) or not (`false`).

fuzzy.description: Indicates how the search engine corrected the misspelled word by using fuzzy logic. It can be a number representing the max number of misspelled letters, or the string `auto` suggesting that the search-engine should set this value by itself.

operator.description:
Indicates how the search-engine dealt with the fullText when there is more than one word.
 * `and` - It means that the products contains all the words in the query.
 * `or` - It means that the results will contain at least one word from the original search query. If `and` was not possible, `or` will be the fallback.

translated.description: Whether the list of products was translated by the IS (`true`) or not (`false`).

mappings.name: Get list of the possible facets for a given query

breadcrumb.description: Generated breadcrumb for the given query.

name.description: Human-readable format of the facet key.

hidden.description: Whether the client-side should hide the facet (`true`) or not (`false`)

name.description: Human-readable format of the facet key.

type.description:
Facet type
 - `TEXT` - The value is a simple text.
 - `PRICERANGE` - The value contains the property `range` representing the minimum and the maximum price for the query.

name.description: Human-readable format of the facet value

selected.description: Whether the value is selected (`true`) or not (`false`).

queryArgs.description: Term and facets used in the query

query.description: Search term used in the query.

sampling.description: Indicates whether there was sampling in the aggregation of facets or not. In search results that have many products, only the first 30000 will be aggregated to avoid performance issues.

mappings.name: Get attempt of correction of a misspelled term

correction.description: Object that indicates if the term was misspelled and suggests a possible correction.
Whether the API was able to suggest a correction (`true`) or not (`false`).

highlighted.description: The same as `text`, but it highlights the corrected word. Useful when there is more than one word.

misspelled.description: Whether the term was misspelled (`true`) or not (`false`).

text.description: The corrected term. If the API was not able to correct the term, it will show the original search term.
